    id: 'ergen:artifacts/flying-swords',
    layer: 'world', category: 'artifacts',
    title: 'Flying Swords',
    subtitle: '飞剑 — Fēi Jiàn',
    body: `Flying Swords are the most iconic artifact of the Ergenverse — and, for many, an entire Dao. A flying sword is not merely a weapon; it is the extension of a sword cultivator's will, riding Qi, cutting distance, and at the highest levels cutting concept, fate, and law itself.

Sword cultivation is a sub-path of artifact refining and a Dao in its own right: the sword-immortal refines a single blade across lifetimes until sword and self are indistinguishable, and a sword-immortal's full-strength strike can sunder mountains or, in legend, the heavens.

Flying swords vary enormously — spirit-wood blades, bone sabers, immortal-metal longswords, sentient swords that choose their masters — and the great sword sects guard their forging lineages as national secrets. In the Azure Cloud World, where Dao Compatibility favors the sword, flying-sword cultivators are disproportionately common, and a Core Formation sword cultivator can duel a Nascent Soul of another path to a standstill. Where the wind whistles and a sword flashes, there walks a sword cultivator.`,
