    subtitle: '储物袋 · 灵舟 — Chǔ Wù Dài · Líng Zhōu',
    body: `Storage artifacts and spirit boats are the everyday miracles of the cultivation world — objects so common they are taken for granted, yet without which the entire economy would collapse. A Storage Pouch or Storage Ring contains a pocket of folded space, allowing a cultivator to carry an entire sect's worth of herbs, beast cores, weapons, and supplies in a single satchel.

The grade of the storage artifact determines its volume, its stability, and whether living things may be carried within (most cannot). Spirit Boats are the great vessels that cross the skies and the Vast Expanse — ranging from a Foundation cultivator's single-person skiff to the sprawling sect flagships that carry hundreds of disciples and bristle with defensive arrays.

Spirit boats often combine all Four Great Arts: artifact hulls, formation engines, talisman ward-sails, alchemical sustenance chambers. To see one pass overhead is to glimpse a small flying city; to ride one is the first true taste of the wider world for any young cultivator of the Azure Cloud.`,
