    subtitle: '远古沉阵 — Yuǎn Gǔ Chén Zhèn',
    body: `Ancient Dormant Arrays are the great sleeping formations of the deep Ergenverse — arrays laid in ages so distant that no sect remembers their makers, embedded in the land itself, awaiting the trigger that will wake them. They are not ruins; they are land.

A mountain range may be the physical inscription of a seal-array laid by a Transcendent against something buried beneath; a sea may be the engine of an ancient formation still slowly gathering Qi for a purpose no living being knows. Such arrays wake for triggers: a specific constellation, a cultivator of a specific bloodline entering their bounds, the breaking of a linked seal elsewhere, or the mere passage of a certain number of years.

When an ancient array wakes, regions reshape — a hidden continent surfaces, a sealed inheritance opens, a Paragon's treasure emerges, or something that should have stayed asleep does not. The Jade-Void Forbidden Land near Mistveil Village is, by rumor, the sleeping node of one such array. The brave and the foolish alike have gone to test the rumor. Most have not returned.`,
