    subtitle: '符箓 — Fú Lù',
    body: `Talismans are the fourth of the Four Great Arts — paper, silk, or jade charms inscribed with condensed Qi and intent, ready to be activated by a single thought. A talisman is, in essence, a technique stored outside the body.

An attack-talisman unleashes a sword-strike without a sword; a defense-talisman raises a barrier without a formation; a transport-talisman flings the user across a hundred li without a flying treasure. Because they are pre-made and one-use (in their lower grades), talismans are the great equalizer of the cultivation world — a Qi Condensation cultivator with a Core-grade attack talisman can, in theory, kill a Core cultivator.

Talisman grades mirror artifact grades: paper → spirit → earth → heaven → immortal, and the highest grades become reusable, sentient, even self-replicating. Talismans are the everyday currency of combat, travel, and commerce; a rogue cultivator's survival often depends more on the depth of his talisman pouch than on the depth of his cultivation.`,
