    subtitle: '符师 — Fú Shī',
    body: `Talisman Masters are the rare cultivators who have made the talisman Dao their primary path — and, in the deepest cases, their primary Dao. A talisman master does not merely inscribe charms; he inscribes law.

At the lowest grades the master produces paper talismans by the hundred for trade; at the middle grades he produces reusable spirit-talismans that bond to a single user; at the highest grades he produces sentient talismans capable of independent judgment, and even talisman-constructs — entire beings made of inscribed law, loyal as a sword, autonomous as a beast.

The talisman Dao pairs naturally with Formation (both are inscription arts) and with Seal (both are bounding arts). Talisman masters are sought as sect-wardens, ruin-breakers, and crafters of the personal defenses carried by every patriarch. A great talisman master can, in extremis, inscribe the air itself with a single character and rewrite the local law for a single instant — the famous "single-stroke talisman" of legend, capable of slaying immortals or sparing the dead.`,
