    subtitle: '宗门 — Zōng Mén',
    body: `Sects are the fundamental political unit of the cultivation world — organized schools of cultivation, lineage, and armed disciples, governing territory, spirit veins, and the mortal cities within their reach.

Sects divide first by alignment — righteous versus demonic — and then by specialization: sword sects, alchemy sects, formation sects, body-cultivation sects, beast-taming sects, and stranger paths. Sect hierarchy ascends from Servant Disciple to Outer, Inner, Core, Elder, Grand Elder, and Patriarch — the founder or senior ancestor who, in smaller sects, may be the only Nascent Soul or higher.

Sects sign non-aggression treaties over veins, "protect" mortal cities in exchange for tribute and labor, wage ruin-opening wars, and seal alliances through Dao-Companion marriages. A Paragon's whim can reshape a continent's sect map overnight. To join a sect is to gain resources, techniques, and protection; to leave one is to lose all three. Most cultivators never leave the sect of their initiation, and most sects outlive their founders by many quiet, quarrelsome centuries.`,
