    id: 'ergen:factions/clans-and-bloodlines',
    layer: 'world', category: 'factions',
    title: 'Clans and Bloodlines',
    subtitle: '家族 — Jiā Zú',
    body: `Clans are the bloodline-based counterpart to sects — extended families whose cultivation is built on inherited technique, inherited bloodline, and inherited grudge. A clan's power derives from its ancestors: a clan that produced one Nascent Soul becomes a regional power for centuries; a clan that produced an Immortal becomes a continental power for millennia.

The great Ancient Clans of the Ergenverse — those that trace their lineage to the Ancient Realm body-stars of God, Devil, and Demon — sit above ordinary clans entirely, treating sects as vassals and Paragons as peers. Most clans are sect vassals: a small family tied to a sect mountain, providing disciples and tribute in exchange for protection.

Clan politics are dynastic and patient; an insult given to a clan's great-grandfather may be avenged by the great-great-grandson two centuries later. Dao Companions within a clan strengthen the bloodline; Dao Companions between clans seal alliances. Blood, in the cultivation world, is a currency older than spirit stones, and the oldest clans count their debts in generations.`,
