    title: 'Rogue Cultivators',
    subtitle: '散修 — Sàn Xiū',
    body: `Rogue Cultivators are the unaffiliated — cultivators without sect, without clan, without inheritance beyond what they have killed for, found, or been granted by chance. They are resource-starved and free.

A rogue's life is hard: no sect vein to cultivate on, no elder to teach, no storage of pills and talismans, no Patriarch to avenge them. In exchange they answer to no one, owe no one, and may go where sect-disciples cannot. Rogues are the prime encounter material of the wilderness — hunters, treasure-seekers, herb-gatherers, ruin-delvers, wandering swordsmen, broken-clan exiles, escaped demonic cultivators, and the occasional hidden Nascent Soul traveling in disguise.

Most die young in the wild; a few, through luck and stubbornness, rise to become the wandering masters of legend. Meng Hao, before he joined the Reliance Sect, was a rogue. Wang Lin, in his long exile, was a rogue. The path is possible. It is merely unforgiving. In the Azure Cloud Region, rogues are common on the trade roads and rare in the deep wild — the wild, after all, belongs to the beasts.`,
