    id: 'ergen:geography/spirit-veins',
    layer: 'world', category: 'geography',
    title: 'Spirit Veins',
    subtitle: '灵脉 — Líng Mài',
    body: `Spirit Veins are the arteries of the cultivation world — underground channels of concentrated Qi along which spirit herbs grow, beasts gather, formations anchor, and sects build. A vein's grade and depth determine everything about the settlement above it.

A heaven-grade vein can sustain a Paragon-sect for ten thousand years; a thin mortal vein can barely sustain a Qi-Condensation hermit. Veins are the first thing a sect claims, the first thing a war is fought over, and the first thing a mortal village is founded upon — Mistveil Village exists because, five hundred years ago, a new vein surfaced here.

Veins can be mined, sealed, broken, exhausted, or migrated; an exhausted vein leaves a dying city; a migrating vein can depopulate a region overnight as sects and clans chase it across the map. The deepest veins, the so-called Dragon-Veins, are said to be alive — sleeping earth-dragons whose dreams are the Qi of an entire continent. To cultivate on a great vein is to drink from a sleeping god.`,
